INSERT INTO `bav3_posts` VALUES (1,3,'2006-12-29 09:31:40','2006-12-29 17:31:40','Welcome you wonderful people, I am very happy that you stopped off to look at this first posting of my newly born blog, what will go here, I have a few ideas but now is not the time nor the place to share them. Hah. My eyes are sore from too many hours in front of this computer diddling and daddling with bits and bobs of website and blog development. I\'m listening to <a href=\"http://www.radioactive.co.nz\">RadioActive</a>, a New Zealand radio station that I have grown attached to for the last couple of years since stumbling upon it somehow... It is fantastically excellent... Right now I must bid you an excellently good night and hit the sack for much needed rest. Until next time. Andrew\n\n\n','Hello world!','','publish','open','open','','hello-world','','','2012-10-17 09:06:46','2012-10-17 09:06:46','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/hello-world/',0,'post','',0),(4,2,'2012-07-29 17:47:51','2012-07-29 17:47:51','[full]\r\n[vcard][name wrapper=\"h1\"][address street=\"40 Hawthorn Place\" town=\"Didcot\" county=\"Oxfordshire\" postcode=\"OX11 6BF\"][email][telephone][/vcard]\r\n[/full]\r\n\r\n[half]\r\n<h2>Personal Statement</h2>\r\nI am a front-end and WordPress developer with four years agency experience looking take the next step in my career. I am passionate about what I do and I love learning new technologies and putting them into use in projects.\r\n[/half]\r\n[full]\r\n<h2>Skills</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Responsive Web Development, including responsive images and SVG</li>\r\n	<li>WordPress Plugin and Theme development</li>\r\n	<li>HTML5, CSS3, PHP, and jQuery</li>\r\n	<li>Accessibility, User Experience and Usability</li>\r\n	<li>Cross-browser and device testing and bug-fixing</li>\r\n	<li>Good knowledge of OOCSS</li>\r\n	<li>Build tools such as Grunt/Gulp/Yeoman to optimise, streamline and standardise code</li>\r\n	<li>DVCS (Git and Mercurial) and SVN</li>\r\n	<li>Continuous deployment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Experience</h2>\r\n\r\n[/full]\r\n[half]\r\n<h3>Electric Studio - <em>Front-end WordPress Developer</em></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>I create WordPress sites directly from Photoshop designs, with custom post-types, taxonomies, meta-boxes, shortcodes and functions.</li>\r\n<li>The focus is to make the site maintainable by the client so everything is manageable without knowing how to code.</li>\r\n<li>The sites are fast loading, using the best technologies and techniques, built within budget and in timeframes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/half]\r\n[half]\r\n<h3>HeathWallace Ltd  <em>Creative developer</em></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>I built highly accessible websites using valid cross-browser tested CSS and HTML for clients including HSBC, RBS and Grant Thornton</li>\r\n	<li>Using CMSs such as WordPress, CQ5 and Sitecore to allow the client to control all content on their site</li>\r\n	<li>Implementing UI functionality utilising in-house jQuery plugins</li>\r\n	<li>Excellent communication with designers, project managers, and fellow dev team members</li>\r\n	<li>Knowledge Sharing through weekly masterclass sessions (I ran three : WordPress; CSS3; and Sass)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/half]\r\n\r\n\r\n[full]\r\n<h2>Relevant Experience</h2>\r\n\r\nHere are a selection of the latest sites that I have made:\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>[website url=\"radiusequity.com\"] - Radius Equity - responsive slick WordPress powered site</li>	\r\n<li>[website url=\"blog.oup.com\"] - OUP Blog - responsive blog built on top of Foundation, and WordPress</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"community.oxforddictionaries.com\"] - Oxford Dictionaries Communities - responsive bbPress powered Forum</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"douglasorde.com\"] - Douglas Orde - high end furniture e-commerce with Woocommerce, SVG, flexbox, calc.</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"accessfertility.co.uk\"] - Access Fertility - responsive WordPress site built with Foundation 4, shortcodes, metaboxes.</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"questraventures.co.uk\"] - Collection of 6 different responsive sites using the same theme with different theme colours utilising Sass variables.</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"thesurfacewithin.co.uk\"] - Highly visual, responsive, site for Minoli\'s high-end London tile showroom.</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"isobelweddings.com\"] - Isobel Weddings - wedding planner based in Oxford</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"satyayoga.co.uk\"] - Satya Yoga - Yoga Company in Oxford</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"printrun.com\"] - Printrun - promotional merchandise for F1 events.</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"adestra.com\"] - Adestra - custom font icons, responsive site for Adestra</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"sarahsflowers.co.uk\"] - Sarah\'s Flowers - Responsive e-commerce site using Woocommerce.</li>\r\n<li>[website url=\"epf.cc\"] - European Property Finance - responsive one page WordPress site with sticky nav and SVG.</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"nationalpersonalsafetyday.co.uk\"] - National Personal Safety Day - Responsive site for event.</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"londonmarine.co.uk\"] - London Marine Consultancy - Marine Consultancy</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"faradion.co.uk\"] - Faradion - advanced, low-cost battery materials</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"opteksystems.com\"] - Optek Systems</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"qatarwhalesharkproject.com/ar\"] - Qatar Whale Shark Research - conversion of theme to arabic (rtl)</li>\r\n<li>[website] - customised responsive WordPress, HTML5, CSS3, Sass, and built with Gulp / Foundation 5, and bower</li>\r\n	<li>[website url=\"github.com/bigandy\"] - My Github account</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/full]\r\n[half]\r\n<h2>Education</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Masters CIW Web Designer</li>\r\n	<li>MChem (hons) Chemistry - University of Manchester</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/half]\r\n[half]\r\n<h2>Interests</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"list-inline\">\r\n	<li>Cycling,</li>\r\n	<li>Running,</li>\r\n	<li>Music</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/half]','CV','','publish','closed','closed','','cv','','','2014-12-16 11:38:37','2014-12-16 11:38:37','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?page_id=4',4,'page','',0),(10,2,'2012-07-29 18:32:24','2012-07-29 18:32:24','[half]\r\n<h1 class=\"h2\">About Me</h1>\r\nMy name is Andrew Hudson and I\'m a front-end web developer based in Oxford, England. Outside of work I love cycling, photography, juggling and listening to music. I\'m married and we have two cats, plus a <a href=\"https://big-andy.co.uk/two-become-three/\">baby on the way</a>.\r\n\r\nI work for <a href=\"http://www.electricstudio.co.uk\">Electric Studio</a> at Milton Park, Oxfordshire as a front-end WordPress developer.\r\n\r\nSpecialising in WordPress theme and plugin development I love working with HTML5, CSS3, PHP and JavaScript.\r\n\r\n[/half]\r\n[half]\r\n<h2 class=\"h3\">Colophon</h2>\r\nThis site is powered by WordPress using <a href=\"https://github.com/markjaquith/WordPress-Skeleton\">WP Skeleton</a> as a template. The theme is built on top of the foundation 5. CSS is pre-compiled by <a href=\"http://gulpjs.com/\">Gulp</a> and <a href=\"http://sass-lang.com/\">Sass</a>.\r\n\r\nThis site is running on <a href=\"http://wiki.nginx.org/Main\">Nginx</a> and is hosted in the Digital Ocean cloud in London.\r\n\r\nI\'ve secured everything with ssl/tls and it utilises <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SPDY\">SPDY</a> v3.1 and it is <strong>https</strong>://big-andy.co.uk.\r\n\r\nCode is tracked using <a href=\"https://github.com/bigandy/big-andy.co.uk\">Github</a>.\r\n\r\nFor the typography <a href=\"http://www.typography.com/fonts/sentinel/styles/\">Sentinel</a> is used for the headings and body, served by <a href=\"http://www.typography.com/cloud/welcome/\">Cloud Typography</a>.\r\n\r\nI am using icons from the <a href=\"http://thenounproject.com/\">Noun Project</a>.\r\n\r\n[/half]\r\n[half]\r\n<h2 class=\"h3\">Links</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"list-plain\">\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://twitter.com/bigandy\">@bigandy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/contact\">Contact Me</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://github.com/bigandy\">github.com/bigandy</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"/feed\">RSS</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/half]','About','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2014-12-16 14:04:35','2014-12-16 14:04:35','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?page_id=10',1,'page','',0),(17,2,'2012-07-29 18:25:03','2012-07-29 18:25:03','','Blog','','publish','closed','open','','blog','','','2014-08-18 21:01:43','2014-08-18 21:01:43','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?page_id=17',2,'page','',0),(19,2,'2012-07-29 18:25:48','2012-07-29 18:25:48',' ','','','publish','open','open','','19','','','2012-07-29 18:27:31','2012-07-29 18:27:31','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?p=19',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(20,3,'2007-02-07 15:16:12','2007-02-07 15:16:12','weds lunchtime and am really feeling like getting out and breathing. The sky is perfectly crystal blue and the air suffocatingly cold, sunshine glistens off the leafless trees while the birds and flowers shiver and wait for spring to arrive. I\'ve not been running in well over two weeks; first of all because I was chronically unwell, then i had a nasty cold and (thus) couldn\'t breath for shit, finally the excuse was the \"couldnotbe arsed\" wildcard, but the power of that is finally waning and I will have to get my skank in gear or I will turn into a slow fat genie but without the bottle. So what is the solution? (1) Badminton this evening; (2) New Running Shoes; (3) Running on Friday... AND\n\n\n\nRemind me that I\'ve got to get the LCD Soundsystem mp3::: \"North American Scum\"::: Pounding Bassline. ingreatness welive.\n\n\n','sugar, lick my salty chocolate balls','','publish','open','open','','sugar-lick-my-salty-chocolate-balls','','','2012-10-17 09:06:45','2012-10-17 09:06:45','',0,'http://www.blog.big-andy.co.uk/2007/02/07/sugar-lick-my-salty-chocolate-balls/',0,'post','',0),(21,2,'2012-07-29 18:27:38','2012-07-29 18:27:38',' ','','','publish','open','open','','21','','','2012-07-29 18:27:38','2012-07-29 18:27:38','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?p=21',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(22,2,'2012-07-29 18:27:49','2012-07-29 18:27:49',' ','','','publish','open','open','','22','','','2012-07-29 18:27:49','2012-07-29 18:27:49','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?p=22',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(23,2,'2012-07-29 18:27:55','2012-07-29 18:27:55',' ','','','publish','open','open','','23','','','2012-07-29 18:30:16','2012-07-29 18:30:16','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?p=23',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(100,2,'2008-01-22 14:38:42','2008-01-22 14:38:42','The nominations for the 80th edition of the Oscars <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/features/rto/2008/oscars\">have been announced</a>','Oscars','','publish','open','open','','oscars','','','2008-01-22 14:38:42','2008-01-22 14:38:42','',0,'http://www.blog.big-andy.co.uk/films/~oscars/',0,'post','',0),(105,2,'2012-08-23 19:51:00','2012-08-23 19:51:00','<h1 class=\"h2\">Photography</h1>\r\n<p>Since I was a wee nipper I\'ve been interested in photography. My Dad, my Grandma and Grandpa all are amazing photographers and during my formative years I was continually surrounded by photography.</p>\r\n<p>When I was living in Cambridge I bought a second-hand film SLR - a Nikon F80 - and I had fun taking photos of life around me.</p>\r\n<p>I have always wanted to learn more about the process of how to take photographs, about sperture, shutter speed and ISO numbers. At the end of 2009 I did a photography course at the local <acronym title=\"Thames Valley University\">TVU</acronym>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>New Photos</h2>\r\n\r\nI\'m currently in the process of improving this site and soon this page will have a selection of my photos. If you want to check out some of my photos please look at my <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/andysan\">photos on flickr</a>.','Photos','','publish','closed','open','','photos','','','2013-11-06 13:41:25','2013-11-06 13:41:25','',0,'http://big-andy.local/?page_id=105',5,'page','',0),(133,2,'2012-08-31 14:48:36','2012-08-31 14:48:36',' ','','','publish','open','closed','','133','','','2014-10-21 21:00:23','2014-10-21 21:00:23','',0,'http://wp.big-andy.co.uk/?p=133',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(172,2,'2012-09-05 16:36:10','2012-09-05 16:36:10','<h1>Contact Me</h1>\r\nYou can contact me via <span data-icon=\"T\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span><a href=\"http://twitter.com/bigandy\" target=\"_blank\">twitter</a>, mobile <a href=\"tel:07736063671\">077 36063 671</a>, or <span data-icon=\"B\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span><a href=\"mailto:andy@big-andy.co.uk\">email</a>','Contact','','publish','closed','closed','','contact','','','2014-07-09 14:23:18','2014-07-09 14:23:18','',0,'http://wp.big-andy.co.uk/?page_id=172',3,'page','',0),(175,2,'2012-09-05 16:36:30','2012-09-05 16:36:30','<label for=\"your-name\">Name:</label>[text* text-608 id:your-name akismet:author]\r\n\r\n<label for=\"your-email\">Email:</label>[email* email-865 id:your-email akismet:author_email]\r\n\r\n<label for=\"your-website\">Website:</label>[text text-812 id:your-website]\r\n\r\n<label for=\"your-message\">Message:</label>[textarea* textarea-70 id:your-message]\r\n\r\n[submit \"Send\"]\n[text-812]\n[text-608] <[email-865]>\nFrom: [text-608] <[email-865]>\r\nSubject: [text-812]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[textarea-70]\r\n\r\n--\r\nThis mail is sent via contact form on big-andy.co.uk\nahudson@gmail.com\n\n\n\n\n[your-subject]\n[your-name] <[your-email]>\nMessage body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n--\r\nThis mail is sent via contact form on big-andy.co.uk http://wp.big-andy.co.uk\n[your-email]\n\n\n\nYour message was sent successfully. Thanks.\nFailed to send your message. Please try later or contact the administrator by another method.\nValidation errors occurred. Please confirm the fields and submit it again.\nPlease accept the terms to proceed.\nEmail address seems invalid.\nPlease fill the required field.\nFailed to upload file.\nThis file type is not allowed.\nThis file is too large.\nFailed to upload file. Error occurred.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nYour answer is not correct.\nFailed to send your message. Please try later or contact the administrator by another method.\nFailed to send your message. Please try later or contact the administrator by another method.','Contact form 1','','publish','closed','closed','','contact-form-1','','','2012-11-06 18:31:33','2012-11-06 18:31:33','',0,'http://wp.big-andy.co.uk/?post_type=wpcf7_contact_form&#038;p=175',0,'wpcf7_contact_form','',0),(182,2,'2008-07-15 08:37:59','2008-07-15 07:37:59','<a href=\"/shared/2008/07/morning.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-183\" title=\"morning\" src=\"/shared/2008/07/morning-300x2001.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\nI am now on two week holiday after 8 gruelling months of getting up at 6am, leaving at 6.30 for 1 hour commute, working till 16.30 and then second 1 hour commute before getting home at 17.30. Knackered, Stressed, Violated, Poluted, Hungry. I now have a new job (just three miles each way) in Reading, starting on the 28th of July, and will get there by bike or by running.\n\n\n\nYesterday I read a lot, used linux (after installing Ubuntu on the computer my brother\'s old computer - cheers <a href=\"http://www.rob-hudson.com\">bro</a>), got infuriated with the noise coming from the knackered fan in said computer (and with Drupal) and set off on my bike to ride to Maplin in search for a replacement fan. The route is the same as I will use for getting to my new job and was really hilly and v.hard work. After finding no suitable fans in the shop I tried a different route home but took a wrong turning and instead of getting the map out I did a bit of high speed exploring, then when knackered got the map out and rode home.\n\n\n\nIn the evening after M had arrived home and we had eaten dinner we watched <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0482088/\">\"Priceless (hors de prix)\"</a>. Really funny film, Audrey Tautou sexy pouting seductive actress in same vain that Audrey Hepburn was in \"Breakfast at Tiffany\'s\"... which reminds me that I have a whole box-set of Audrey Hepburn films to watch.\n\n\n','Good Morning World','','publish','open','open','','good-morning-world','','','2012-11-01 15:30:13','2012-11-01 15:30:13','',0,'http://www.blog.big-andy.co.uk/?p=182',0,'post','',0),(185,2,'2008-07-24 11:31:40','2008-07-24 10:31:40','<a href=\"/shared/2008/07/p1000891.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-188\" title=\"en haut de la tour eiffel\" src=\"/shared/2008/07/p1000891-300x2251.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n\n\nwelcome back to this blog after a day off-line. Tried to upgrade Wordpress (the strings that hold this blog together) from version 2.5.1 to 2.6 but must have got something wrong. So still with 2.5.1 for now.<span style=\"color: red;\">&lt;update&gt; now have upgraded to 2.6 not that difficult really.&lt;/update&gt;</span>\n\n\n\nBack home after a week in Paris for friends wedding. We took Eurostar last Weds then met up with Didier and Lucie at their home in the suburbs. Thu M and I went into Paris and did some touristy leg-walking, mission number one the Eiffel Tower then mission number 2: find some churros. Both accomplished but the second only just as we almost ran out of energy after walking at least 10km in our search. Fri spent preparing for the marriage and then Sat morning too, before the wedding and eating drinking and partying into early hours. Sun cleaning up then on Monday went to Paris again to walk to Monmartre and then to Line, Jabert and Lisa\'s to collect our bags before catching the Eurostar back to UK.\n\n\n','TFFT','','publish','open','open','','tfft','','','2012-11-01 15:30:17','2012-11-01 15:30:17','',0,'http://www.blog.big-andy.co.uk/?p=185',0,'post','',0),(192,2,'2012-09-07 10:23:38','2012-09-07 10:23:38','','jupiterfull','','inherit','closed','closed','','jupiterfull','','','2012-09-07 10:23:38','2012-09-07 10:23:38','',0,'/shared/2012/09/jupiterfull.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(194,2,'2012-09-07 10:31:53','2012-09-07 10:31:53',