e</li>\n	<li>DVCS (Git and Mercurial) and SVN</li>\n	<li>Continuous deployment</li>\n</ul>\n[/half]\n[full]\n\n<h2>Experience</h2>\n\n[/full]\n[half]\n<h3>Electric Studio - <em>Front-end WordPress Developer</em></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>I create WordPress sites directly from Photoshop designs, with custom post-types, taxonomies, meta-boxes, shortcodes and functions.</li>\n<li>The focus is to make the site maintainable by the client so everything is manageable without knowing how to code.</li>\n<li>The sites are fast loading, using the best technologies and techniques, built within budget and in timeframes.</li>\n</ul>\n[/half]\n[half]\n<h3>HeathWallace Ltd  <em>Creative developer</em></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>I built highly accessible websites using valid cross-browser tested CSS and HTML for clients including HSBC, RBS and Grant Thornton</li>\n	<li>Using CMSs such as WordPress, CQ5 and Sitecore to allow the client to control all content on their site</li>\n	<li>Implementing UI functionality utilising in-house jQuery plugins</li>\n	<li>Excellent communication with designers, project managers, and fellow dev team members</li>\n	<li>Knowledge Sharing through weekly masterclass sessions (I ran three : WordPress; CSS3; and Sass)</li>\n</ul>\n[/half]\n\n\n[full]\n<h2>Relevant Experience</h2>\n\nHere are a selection of the latest sites that I have made:\n\n<ul>\n<li>[website url=\"radiusequity.com\"] - Radius Equity - responsive slick WordPress powered site</li>	\n<li>[website url=\"blog.oup.com\"] - OUP Blog - responsive blog built on top of Foundation, and WordPress</li>\n<li>[website url=\"community.oxforddictionaries.com\"] - Oxford Dictionaries Communities - responsive bbPress powered Forum</li>\n<li>[website url=\"douglasorde.com\"] - Douglas Orde - high end furniture e-commerce with Woocommerce, SVG, flexbox, calc.</li>\n<li>[website url=\"accessfertility.co.uk\"] - Access Fertility - responsive WordPress site built with Foundation 4, shortcodes, metaboxes.</li>\n<li>[website url=\"questraventures.co.uk\"] - Collection of 6 different responsive sites using the same theme with different theme colours utilising Sass variables.</li>\n<li>[website url=\"thesurfacewithin.co.uk\"] - Highly visual, responsive, site for Minoli\'s high-end London tile showroom.</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"isobelweddings.com\"] - Isobel Weddings - wedding planner based in Oxford</li>\n<li>[website url=\"satyayoga.co.uk\"] - Satya Yoga - Yoga Company in Oxford</li>\n<li>[website url=\"printrun.com\"] - Printrun - promotional merchandise for F1 events.</li>\n<li>[website url=\"adestra.com\"] - Adestra - custom font icons, responsive site for Adestra</li>\n<li>[website url=\"sarahsflowers.co.uk\"] - Sarah\'s Flowers - Responsive e-commerce site using Woocommerce.</li>\n<li>[website url=\"epf.cc\"] - European Property Finance - responsive one page WordPress site with sticky nav and SVG.</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"nationalpersonalsafetyday.co.uk\"] - National Personal Safety Day - Responsive site for event.</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"londonmarine.co.uk\"] - London Marine Consultancy - Marine Consultancy</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"faradion.co.uk\"] - Faradion - advanced, low-cost battery materials</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"opteksystems.com\"] - Optek Systems</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"qatarwhalesharkproject.com/ar\"] - Qatar Whale Shark Research - conversion of theme to arabic (rtl)</li>\n<li>[website] - customised responsive WordPress, HTML5, CSS3, Sass, and built with Gulp / Foundation 5, and bower</li>\n	<li>[website url=\"github.com/bigandy\"] - My Github account</li>\n</ul>\n[/full]\n[half]\n<h2>Education</h2>\n<ul>\n	<li>Masters CIW Web Designer</li>\n	<li>MChem (hons) Chemistry - University of Manchester</li>\n</ul>\n[/half]\n[half]\n<h2>Interests</h2>\n<ul class=\"list-inline\">\n	<li>Cycling,</li>\n	<li>Running,</li>\n	<li>Music</li>\n</ul>\n[/half]','CV','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-16 11:37:49','2014-12-16 11:37:49','',4,'http://andyhudson.me/blog/4-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1900,3,'2012-11-05 11:58:08','2012-11-05 11:58:08','<p>Following up from my decision to <a href=\"http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/changing-web-hosts/\">change web host</a> I have decided to go with AWS. Now I\'ve migrated this site to a Amazon Web Services (AWS) EC2 Micro instance (free for 1 year) and after getting used to the different way of doing things (control is all command line, no web interface at all) I\'m extremely happy with the outcome.</p>\n\n<p>The server is in the cloud (in Ireland - they have lots of clouds in Ireland as it rains a lot) and on a non-shared host it\'s much much faster (for me in England) and I am getting to learn more about Apache and MySQL and command line.</p>\n\n<p>There are a few things that I need to figure out : setting permissions while doing a Capistrano deploy, setting up email (for the Contact Form).</p>\n\n<p>I\'m still migrating sites over from one host to the other so the Photos are currently not accessible.</p>\n','Moving to AWS','','publish','open','closed','','moving-to-aws','','','2012-12-08 21:36:12','2012-12-08 21:36:12','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1900',0,'post','',0),(1902,2,'2012-11-05 11:59:11','2012-11-05 11:59:11','Following up from my decision to <a href=\"http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/web-hosts/\" title=\"Web Hosts\">move away from Dreamhost</a> So now this site is hosted on Amazon Web Services (AWS) EC2 Micro instance (free for 1 year) and after getting used to the different way of doing things (control is all command line, no web interface at all) I\'m extremely happy with the outcome.\n\n\n\nThe server is in the cloud (in Ireland) and on a non-shared host it\'s much much faster (for me in England) and I am getting to learn more about Apache and MySQL and command line. There are a few things that I need to figure out : setting permissions while doing a Capistrano deploy, setting up email (for the Contact Form). I\'m still migrating sites over from one host to the other so the Photos are currently not accessible.\n\n\n','Moving to AWS','','inherit','closed','closed','','1900-autosave','','','2012-11-05 11:59:11','2012-11-05 11:59:11','',1900,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1900-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1913,3,'2012-11-05 16:49:42','2012-11-05 16:49:42','<p>Winter seems to have arrived early bringing cold air inside and out.<!--more--> Currently I\'m freezing my arse off at the office at work and after work I\'m going to go running with my friend Ale.</p>\n','Cold Feet','','publish','open','closed','','cold-feet','','','2012-12-08 21:36:12','2012-12-08 21:36:12','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1913',0,'post','',0),(1917,3,'2012-11-06 11:22:02','2012-11-06 11:22:02','<p>http://vimeo.com/channels/fronteers12/52851509</p>\n','Ten Things you didn\'t know about HTML','','private','open','closed','','ten-things-you-didnt-know-about-html','','','2012-12-08 21:36:12','2012-12-08 21:36:12','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1917',0,'post','',0),(1926,2,'2012-11-06 22:46:32','2012-11-06 22:46:32','<h2>Digital Photography Course</h2>\n<p>Since I was a wee nipper I\'ve been interested in photography. My Dad, my Grandma and Grandpa all are amazing photographers and during my formative years I was continually surrounded by photography.</p>\n<p>When I was living in Cambridge I bought a second-hand film SLR - a Nikon F80 - and I had fun taking photos of life around me.</p>\n<p>I have always wanted to learn more about the process of how to take photographs, about sperture, shutter speed and ISO numbers. At the end of 2009 I did a photography course at the local <acronym title=\"Thames Valley University\">TVU</acronym>.</p>\n\n<h2>New Photos</h2>\n\nI\'m currently in the process of improving this site and soon this page will have a selection of my photos. If you want to check out some of my photos please look at my photos on flickr.','Photos','','inherit','open','closed','','105-autosave-v1','','','2012-11-06 22:46:32','2012-11-06 22:46:32','',105,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/105-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(1939,2,'2012-10-30 16:59:13','2012-10-30 16:59:13','It seems to me that the future of front-end development is with JavaScript and that now is a good time to become much better at writing and using it. So to aid my knowledge I\'ve just started to read the book <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/JavaScript-Good-Parts-Douglas-Crockford/dp/0596517742\">JavaScript: The Good Parts</a> by Douglas Crockford. I am also starting to learn about the <a href=\"http://http://backbonejs.org/\">Backbone.js library</a>. I spoke to a colleague today in the JS team here at work and he said the best way to learn about it is to make something with it so hopefully soon I\'ll have something to show!\n\n\n','JavaScript : the Good Parts','','inherit','open','closed','','1788-revision','','','2012-10-30 16:59:13','2012-10-30 16:59:13','',1788,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1788-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1940,2,'2012-10-29 10:26:35','2012-10-29 10:26:35','Today marks the end of British Summer Time (BST) and start of Reading Half-marathon training. Today also marks 140 days until the race and its the first time I\'ve run in over a month. Just a small run to get me back into it and I plan to go running on Tuesday to continue my training process. Start small aim big! Looking forward to Tuesday!\n\n\n','140 days - Reading Half Marathon','','inherit','open','closed','','1784-revision','','','2012-10-29 10:26:35','2012-10-29 10:26:35','',1784,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1784-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1941,2,'2012-10-27 16:43:05','2012-10-27 16:43:05','I\'ve been a member of the Rough Trade Album Club for the last year and not really listened to all the CDs so this afternoon while trying out my new desk chair and tidying the office I\'m listening to <strong>all</strong> of them!\n\n\n','Music - a year in retrospective','','inherit','open','closed','','1781-revision','','','2012-10-27 16:43:05','2012-10-27 16:43:05','',1781,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1781-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1943,2,'2012-10-24 12:54:34','2012-10-24 12:54:34','Every year since the first time that I went to see the Tour de France go up Alpe d\'Huez in 2003 - I\'ve wanted to go back to France and see some more live action. I managed to see it when in 2007 it came to London but not been over to see it in France. Until now.\n\n\n\nMy wife Marion, my bro Rob, and my cousins\' boyfriends Rich and Nick are all planning to go and see some stages of next years - the 100<sup>th</sup> edition - race.\n\n\n\nFor <a href=\"http://inrng.com/2012/10/2013-tour-de-france/\">full stage details check this inrng post</a>\n\n\n','The 2013 Tour de France','The route of the 100th edition of the Tour de France has just been released and Marion, Rob, Rich, Nick <span class=\"amp\">&amp;</span> I are planning to see some action.','inherit','open','closed','','1768-revision','','','2012-10-24 12:54:34','2012-10-24 12:54:34','',1768,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1768-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1945,2,'2012-10-24 10:29:29','2012-10-24 10:29:29','Today is my 32nd birthday and I am at work bug fixing. Marion made me an excellent (chocolate!) birthday cake and tonight a surprise is planned.\n\n\n','Birthday #32','','inherit','open','closed','','1762-revision','','','2012-10-24 10:29:29','2012-10-24 10:29:29','',1762,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1762-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1946,2,'2012-10-23 14:08:07','2012-10-23 14:08:07','Right now listening to the <a href=\"http://5by5.tv/bigwebshow/74\">latest Big Web Show</a> with <a href=\"http://css-tricks.com/\">Chris Coyier</a> being interviewed by <a href=\"http://www.zeldman.com/\">Jeffrey Zeldman</a>\n\n\n','Chris Coyier - Big Web Show','','inherit','open','closed','','1755-revision','','','2012-10-23 14:08:07','2012-10-23 14:08:07','',1755,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1755-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1948,2,'2012-10-19 10:15:49','2012-10-19 10:15:49','Yesterday I read that the Guardian website is <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/developer-blog/2012/oct/18/responsive-design-guardian-introduction\">currently being re-developed</a> and is <a href=\"http://beta.guardian.co.uk\">currently in Beta</a>.\n\n\n\nThe site is going to be responsive, mobile first, using <a href=\"http://smacss.com/\">SMACSS</a> (a OOCSS methodology which I am currently reading up on) and <a href=\"http://requirejs.org/\">requirejs</a>. It is incredibly fast and from my point of view it looks beautiful.\n\n\n','Beta Guardian Site','','inherit','open','closed','','1722-revision','','','2012-10-19 10:15:49','2012-10-19 10:15:49','',1722,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1722-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1949,2,'2012-10-19 13:29:45','2012-10-19 13:29:45','<h2>Intro</h2>\n\nNow that I have released the newly re-developed and imagined v3 of the big-andy.co.uk site (which will remain a work in progress for the next months while I tweek and tame the site) I am going to keep a list of outstanding items that I feel need to be done.\n\n\n\n<h3>Optimisation</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T17:45:41+00:00\">Use w3tc plugin</del></li>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-16T16:24:00+00:00\">combine plugin css and js into this theme css and js. This will reduce the number of http requests and hopefully speed up the site.</del></li>\n<li>Reduce number of DB queries (if possible)</li>\n<li>Get minify working if possible </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Security</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>lock-down the admin area (either by .htaccess or .htpassword)</li>\n<li>prevent admin from publishing posts (have user andrew-hudson do this)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Writing</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T17:45:41+00:00\">use markdown</del></li>\n<li>Try and write more often - practice makes the process become more natural!</li>\n    <li>Write posts from mobile and iPad</li>\n    <li>Disable admin from publishing posts</li>\n\n\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Photos</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use a CPT and custom taxonomy</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>SEO</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use WordPress SEO Plugin</li>\n<li>Use Google XML Sitemaps Plugin</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Backup and DB Optimisation</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T17:45:41+00:00\">Use BackWPup plugin</del></li>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T17:45:41+00:00\">Use Git</del></li>\n<li>Use DB Optimise plugin</li>\n</ul>\n','v3 ToDo List','','inherit','open','closed','','1574-revision','','','2012-10-19 13:29:45','2012-10-19 13:29:45','',1574,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1574-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1951,2,'2012-10-16 08:49:32','2012-10-16 08:49:32','Looking forward to going to Gathering festival this Saturday in Oxford. Features bands including George Ezra, Swiss Lips and Paws.\n\n\n\n<!--more-->\n\n<a href=\"http://gatheringfestival.tumblr.com/\">Gathering Festival - October 20th - various venues in Oxford</a>\n\n\n','Gathering Festival this weekend','','inherit','open','closed','','1433-revision','','','2012-10-16 08:49:32','2012-10-16 08:49:32','',1433,'http://big-andy.co.uk/blog/1433-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(1959,3,'2012-11-15 11:55:36','2012-11-15 11:55:36','<p>Last night was my first time with the work running club and we did 7.6 miles around Caversham and West Reading in 1:10:41 with some hills and lots of pavements.</p>\n','HW Running Club','','publish','open','closed','','hw-running-club','','','2012-12-08 21:36:11','2012-12-08 21:36:11','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1959',0,'post','',0),(1966,3,'2012-11-19 14:36:43','2012-11-19 14:36:43','http://vimeo.com/53155584\r\n','Jason Santa Maria : Saying No','','publish','open','closed','','jason-santa-maria-saying-no','','','2012-12-09 12:53:18','2012-12-09 12:53:18','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1966',0,'post','',0),(1970,3,'2012-11-27 20:37:19','2012-11-27 20:37:19','<p>Last five weeks have been really good as I have been running on average least twice a week every week since October 28th when I woke up early to go running along the river. I have been helped by going running with a friend and also the work running club. It helps with the motivation if you have other people to go running with - at least in the tricky first month.</p>\n\n<p>What differences have I noticed? Well the first couple of weeks I had bad shin spint in my right shin and this slowed me down. I\'ve not lost weight but I have lost a bit of fat on my tummy. I\'m more confident to go longer distances than I ever was before, I used to cringe at the thought of running 5 miles but I have done that on five of the running sessions, the furthest was 7.6 miles with the work club.</p>\n\n<p>I think I prefer running long distances and seeing how far I can run. Obviously re-starting running is initially to train for the Reading Half-Marathon next March (now 110 days away) but sometime I\'d like to see if I could run further...possibly one day even a marathon.</p>\n','Running - Five weeks','','publish','open','closed','','running-five-weeks','','','2012-12-08 21:36:11','2012-12-08 21:36:11','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1970',0,'post','',0),(1973,3,'2012-11-28 14:14:42','2012-11-28 14:14:42','<p>This afternoon Marion took the cats to the vet and what we thought once as two boy kittens are now \"girls\". So Inti and Punku are girls!</p>\n','Two Girl Kittens','','publish','open','closed','','two-girl-kittens','','','2012-12-08 21:36:11','2012-12-08 21:36:11','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1973',0,'post','',0),(1976,3,'2012-11-30 16:40:00','2012-11-30 16:40:00','<p>Today is St Andrew\'s Day and as my name is Andrew I\'m wishing all other Andrews a happy St Andrews!</p>\n','Happy St.Andrew\'s Day!','','publish','open','closed','','happy-st-andrews-day','','','2012-12-08 21:36:11','2012-12-08 21:36:11','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?p=1976',0,'post','',0),(1978,3,'2012-12-04 16:20:21','2012-12-04 16:20:21','<p>Last night I went for my longest run since Feb with 10.4 miles through Caversham, Emmer Green and along the flooded river.</p>\n','Monday Long Run','','publish','open','closed','','monday-lon