bass is deeper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h5\">Coding</h2>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sublimetext.com/\">Sublime Text</a> is the best text editor I\'ve ever used. Currently I\'m using <a href=\"http://www.sublimetext.com/3\">Sublime Text 3 beta</a>. Combined with this I use LiveReload to update the browser window when I make a file edit (rather than going from one text-editor to browser pressing reload EVERY time I make a small change. Now it\'s instant!)\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h5\">Version Control</h2>\r\n\r\nI use Git and to manage this I use Sourcetree. I do use the command line but when there\'s lots of different projects, many file changes its easier to see it all in one place with the GUI of Sourcetree. It saves a lot of typing! \r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h5\">Sass / Compass / Grunt</h2>\r\n\r\nI\'ve been using Sass for close to two years now and I love it. Saves much time and allows you to focus on writing clean fast code. \r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h5\">WordPress</h2>\r\n\r\nI\'m a professional WordPress developer concentrating on front-end but also able to write plugins and more advanced stuffs with databases.\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h5\">Apps I use</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sublime Text 3 (beta)</li>\r\n	<li>Spotify</li>\r\n	<li>LiveReload (mac app)</li>\r\n	<li>Chrome Canary (has better dev tools vs. regular Chrome)\r\n		<ul>\r\n			<li>LiveReload</li>\r\n			<li>Chrome Nanny - mainly to block Facebook and Twitter!</li>\r\n			<li>1Password</li>\r\n			<li>Awesome Screenshot - take screenshots when need to show client specifics</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Twitterific - awesome app for twitter (mac app)</li>\r\n	<li>1Password - store all the passwords to everything.</li>\r\n	<li>SourceTree - Version Control</li>\r\n	<li>Bartender - app for hiding menu items and makes the desktop window a minimalistic distraction free zone (mac app)</li>\r\n	<li>iA Writer - distraction-free content first writing environment (mac app)</li>\r\n	<li>iTerm 2 - an incredible alternative to terminal (mac app)</li>\r\n</ul>','The Tools I use','','private','closed','closed','','the-tools-i-use','','','2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','',0,'http://big-andy.co.uk/?page_id=2194',0,'page','',0),(2198,2,'2013-05-15 14:15:42','2013-05-15 14:15:42','Every developer has their own favourite tools and these are mine. \r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h4\">Music</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Decent music (currently I\'m using Spotify because of the huge variety of available music, the ability to sync and upload music onto my phone - great for the commute to work))</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Decent headphones (to listen to music and also to block unwanted distractions - colleagues on the phone or ice-cream van outside) I\'m using <a href=\"http://www.amazon.co.uk/Sennheiser-CX300-II-Precision-bass-driven/dp/B001EZYMF4\">Sennheiser CX300 II</a></li>\r\n\r\n<li>Digital Analogue Convertor (DAC) - I\'m using <a href=\"http://fiio.com.cn/products/index.aspx?ID=100000028262517\">Fiio Olympus E10</a> - and its a huge difference in sound quality that I get from my computer. The sound is warmer, cleaner and the bass is deeper.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nCoding\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sublimetext.com/\">Sublime Text</a> is the best text editor I\'ve ever used. Currently I\'m using <a href=\"http://www.sublimetext.com/3\">Sublime Text 3 beta</a>. Combined with this I use LiveReload to update the browser window when I make a file edit (rather than going from one text-editor to browser pressing reload EVERY time I make a small change. Now it\'s instant!)\r\n\r\nVersion Control\r\n\r\nI use Git and to manage this I use Sourcetree. I do use the command line but when there\'s lots of different projects, many file changes its easier to see it all in one place with the GUI of Sourcetree. It saves a lot of typing! \r\n\r\nSass / Compass / Grunt\r\n\r\nI\'ve been using Sass for close to two years now and I love it. Saves much time and allows you to focus on writing clean fast code. \r\n\r\nWordPress \r\n\r\nI\