I\'ll add more here as and when I find them)\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"h3\">OOCSS</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"list-plain\">\r\n<li><a href=\"http://nicolasgallagher.com/about-html-semantics-front-end-architecture/\">Nicolas Gallagher - About HTML semantics  and front-end architecture</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://beta.guardian.co.uk/\">beta.guardian.co.uk site</a> <span class=\"amp\">&amp;</span> <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/help/developer-blog/2012/oct/18/responsive-design-guardian-introduction\">Introduction to Beta.guardian.co.uk</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/csswizardry/inuit.css\">inuit.css</a> which is an oocss framework built using Sass.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://smacss.com/\">SMACSS - Scalable Modular Architecture for CSS</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<!-- nextpage this is currently not working on the \"thoughts\" template as there is no code for it-->\r\n\r\n<h2 class=h3>HTML5</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2 class=h3>JavaScript <span class=amp>&amp;</span> jQuery</h2>','Development Tools','','inherit','closed','closed','','1731-revision-v1','','','2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','',1731,'http://big-andy.co.uk/1731-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2388,2,'2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','','Blog','','inherit','closed','closed','','17-revision-v1','','','2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','',17,'http://big-andy.co.uk/17-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2389,2,'2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','This is the third version of <a href=\"http://big-andy.co.uk\" title=\"personal site of Andrew Hudson\">big-andy.co.uk</a> and I want to detail how I made it.\r\n\r\n<h2>History</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Version one</h3>\r\n\r\nThe first version of big-andy.co.uk was made totally with html and css and because it was so poor I don\'t have an archived version of it. I made it before I begun learning about accessibility and usability, WordPress and web standards. It was just somewhere I could put photos. \r\n\r\n<h3>Version two</h3>\r\n\r\nVersion two of big-andy.co.uk can now be <a href=\"http://archive.big-andy.co.uk/v2/\" title=\"big-andy.co.uk v2\">found here</a> and was build with html/css/php and the seperate blog (on its own sub-domain) blog.big-andy.co.uk was powered by WordPress. \r\n\r\nI used some CSS3, HTML5 and implemented my burgeoning knowledge of web-design, development and web-standards. \r\n\r\nI built v2 two years old, before getting my first job in web development and now decided that now it needed a face-lift. \r\n\r\n<h2>v3</h2>\r\n\r\nThe third version of my site is a strong change from the precious two versions. First of all I wanted it to be built 100% with WordPress because that is the CMS the I have learnt to use and love.\r\n\r\nI\'m using Git to do the code version control, Capistrano to handle the deployments, Sass to precompile the CSS, and also incorporating all the skills that I learnt during the last two years to pimp this site including security, plugin and theme development and code optimisation.\r\n\r\n<h2>Browser support</h2>\r\n\r\nAs this is my own site I decided that I would only support IE9+, latest version of Firefox, Chrome, Opera and be responsive so works on mobile and tablet devices. If you spot a bug please <a href=\"http://big-andy.co.uk/contact/\">drop me line via the contact form</a>','Big Andy v3','','inherit','closed','closed','','1341-revision-v1','','','2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','',1341,'http://big-andy.co.uk/1341-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2390,2,'2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','It\'s always interesting to see how others work. Perhaps we can pick up some tips or find out about tools that\'ll help our working lives.\n\n\n\n<h2>Browsers</h2>\n\nI\'m a huge fan of Chrome after many years of Firefox use. Simply arrived one day at work (July 2012) and decided to use Chrome and haven\'t looked back. Takes up less screen space, and is faster than Firefox.\n\n\n\n<h3>Browser Add-ons</h3>\n\n<ul>\n<li>1password - to keep track of all my passwords </li>\n<li>AdBlock - blocks adds on websites </li>\n<li>liveReload - automatically re-loads a page when code is edited in Sublime Text 2. Awesome! </li>\n<li>Nanny for Google Chrome - stops me from using specific sites (Facebook and Twitter) so I can focus on working </li>\n<li>Awesome Screenshot: Capture &amp; Annotate - taking screenshots </li>\n<li>Type-ahead-find - copies Firefox\'s find as you type functionality </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Code editing</h2>\n\nThe path that I\'ve followed is this :\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T10:42:44+00:00\">Notepad</del></li>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T10:42:44+00:00\">Notepad++</del></li>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T10:42:44+00:00\">Dreamweaver</del></li>\n<li><del datetime=\"2012-10-18T10:42:44+00:00\">Aptana Studio 3</del></li>\n<li>Sublime Text 2 </li>\n</ol>\n\nThe best I\'ve ever used is Sublime Text 2 followed at a distance by Aptana.\n\n\n\n<h2>Version Control</h2>\n\nAt work we use Mercurial and at home I use Git. I love them both.\n\n\n','How I work','','inherit','closed','closed','','443-revision-v1','','','2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','',443,'http://big-andy.co.uk/443-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(2391,2,'2013-12-11 18:33:14','2013-12-11 18:33:14','So. Coming up with two names for the Kittens that we\'re getting next week (2 black ones from this photo). \r\n<a href=\"/shared/2012/09/photo.jpg\"><img src=\"/shared/2012/09/photo.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"kittens-and-mother\" width=\"640\" height=\"428\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-287\" /></a>\r\nHere\'s the list of suggestions from the tea group at work:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Fabio and Grooverider</li>\r\n	<li>Lennox Lewis and Mike Tyson</li>\r\n	<li>Tupac and Tupac 2</li>\r\n	<li>Frankie and Benny</li>\r\n	<li>Snowy and Whitey</li>\r\n	<li>Onepac and Tupac</li>\r\n	<li>Stinky and Chicken</li>\r\n	<li>Barry and Paul</li>\r\n	<li>Jules and Verne</li>\r\n	<li>Firefox and Wetfox</li>\r\n	<li>Shimano and Dunlop</li>